 if fuzz targets exist in source tree\n   - Need to understand Dovecot\'s fuzzing build system\n\n### **Diagnostic Questions:**\n1. What does `--with-fuzzer=clang` actually do in Dovecot\'s configure script?\n2. Are there any existing fuzz target source files in the Dovecot repository?\n3. Does Dovecot have a fuzzing test suite or fuzzing infrastructure?\n4. How are fuzz targets supposed to be built in Dovecot?\n\n### **Recommended Investigation Steps:**\n1. **Examine configure.ac for fuzzer support**:\n   - Search for `--with-fuzzer` option definition\n   - Check what build flags it sets\n   - See if it enables building of fuzz targets\n\n2. **Search for existing fuzz files**:\n   - Look for `fuzz-*` source files in the repository\n   - Check if there\'s a `fuzz/` directory\n   - Look for fuzzing-related test files\n\n3. **Check OSS-Fuzz history**:\n   - Look at how Dovecot fuzzing was previously configured\n   - Check if there are existing fuzz targets in OSS-Fuzz\n\n4. **Simplify Approach**:\n   - Instead of creating complex fuzz targets from scratch\n   - Focus on enabling existing fuzzing support\n   - Or create minimal fuzz targets that test core functionality\n\n### **Expert Recommendation**:\nFocus on understanding Dovecot\'s fuzzing infrastructure:\n1. First, check what `--with-fuzzer=clang` actually enables\n2. Look for existing fuzz targets or fuzzing infrastructure\n3. If none exist, create simple fuzz targets for core protocols (IMAP, SMTP parsing)\n4. Ensure fuzz targets are built and copied to `/out/`\n\n**Critical**: The previous attempt at creating complex fuzz targets failed due to complexity overload. A simpler approach is needed.\n\n--- 【LESSONS FROM PREVIOUS ATTEMPTS】 ---\n- [Attempt 1] The build failed at Docker image creation stage with "Cannot use local checkout with WORKDIR: /src". This is a configuration issue where the OSS-Fuzz build system cannot mount the local project source when WORKDIR is set to /src. The original error was a compilation error in fuzz_pdfload.cc (displayPage function call mismatch), but now we have a regression to an earlier Docker configuration error. The issue appears to be with the OSS-Fuzz build system\'s interaction with the Dockerfile WORKDIR directive when using local checkouts.\n- [Attempt 1] Original build failed with missing ldap.h header (LDAP development libraries not installed). Current build appears to complete compilation successfully with warnings but no fatal errors. The fix likely involved installing LDAP dev packages. However, decision_agent indicates build still failed, possibly due to no fuzz targets being found/copied to /out/. Lesson: Missing system dependencies (ldap.h) can be resolved by installing appropriate dev packages, but need to verify fuzz target generation and copying.\n- [Attempt 2] LDAP dependency fixed successfully (libldap2-dev installed, --with-ldap=plugin added). Compilation now completes without ldap.h error. However, fuzz targets still not generated. Attempt to create fuzz source files failed due to missing directory structure and patch mismatches. The core issue remains: Dovecot\'s --with-fuzzer=clang configure option doesn\'t actually build executables named \'fuzz-*\'. Lesson: Need to investigate what --with-fuzzer=clang actually does in Dovecot\'s build system instead of creating custom fuzz targets. Complexity overload from attempting too many file modifications at once.\n\n\n--- Configuration Files (Dockerfile, build.sh, etc.) ---\n\n### Content from: Dockerfile ###\n# Copyright 2020 Google Inc.\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\nFROM gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder@sha256:b79d3707eeffb6c75a530689b5ade9038bd005628f44d30c62680f4b810c3900\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y make autoconf automake libtool wget gettext automake libxml2-dev m4 pkg-config bison flex python3.8-venv libssl-dev zlib1g-dev libldap2-dev\nRUN git clone  https://github.com/dovecot/core dovecot\nWORKDIR dovecot\nCOPY build.sh $SRC/\n#COPY fuzz-* $SRC/\n\n\n### Content from: build.sh ###\n#!/bin/bash -eu\n# Copyright 2020 Google Inc.\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n./autogen.sh\n./configure PANDOC=false --with-fuzzer=clang --with-ldap=plugin\nmake\n\n# Copy over the fuzzers\nfind . -name "fuzz-*" -executable -exec cp {} $OUT/ \\;\n\n### Content from: project.yaml ###\nhomepage: "https://www.dovecot.org/"\nlanguage: c\nprimary_contact: "oss-fuzz@open-xchange.com"\nauto_ccs:\n    - "david@adalogics.com"\n    - "p.antoine@catenacyber.fr"\n    - "cmousefi@gmail.com"\n    - "boschstephan@gmail.com"\n    - "timo.sirainen@gmail.com"\nmain_repo: \'https://github.com/dovecot/core\'\n\nfuzzing_engines:\n  - afl\n  - honggfuzz\n  - libfuzzer\n\n\n\n--- Project File Tree (Shallow View) ---\n📁 dovecot\n├── 📄 AUTHORS\n├── 📄 COPY